author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "extract output uses current referenced_entities/referenced_devices/referenced_areas and missing fields; related registry lookups consume current fields; target triggers, conditions, and services commands are documented, help-complete, type-safe, unit-tested, and live-tested"
definition_of_ready: Official current WebSocket target helper contract and live instance behavior captured
value: Agents can reason about valid automations for a target without constructing raw WebSocket JSON
impact: "Improves deterministic planning, reduces invalid service calls, and fixes empty related results"
outcome: Target selectors resolve to correct related resources and applicable automation primitives
why_now: Current helper reads obsolete keys and omits two official discovery commands
parent: hac-n0ix
reviewer: unbraind
risk: medium
confidence: high
release: 2026.7.22
resolution: "Added typed extract, trigger, condition, service, and related-registry commands using current Home Assistant response fields and selector semantics."
expected_result: Typed WebSocket target helpers match the current Home Assistant protocol and provide complete agent discovery primitives.
actual_result: All 58 linked WebSocket tests and the complete live target-discovery E2E workflow pass on the local instance.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:39:49.688Z",codex-root,Live target discovery confirms extract_from_target returns referenced_entities referenced_devices referenced_areas and missing arrays; get_triggers_for_target get_conditions_for_target and get_services_for_target return arrays and default expand_group to true.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:59:13.629Z",codex-root,"The official response contract uses referenced_entities, referenced_devices, referenced_areas plus missing_* arrays; the current related helper reads entity_ids/device_ids/area_ids/floor_ids/label_ids."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:59:14.729Z",codex-root,"Generic ws call preserves forward compatibility, while typed target commands are still valuable for discoverability, validation, and low-token agent workflows."
  "2026-07-21T20:36:55.132Z",codex-root,"Current Home Assistant target extraction returns referenced entity/device/area sets plus missing selectors; related registry lookup must consume those current fields, and agent planning benefits from typed trigger, condition, and service discovery beside extraction."
